how does the it services software licensing office choose which software to site license stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how does the it services software licensing office choose which software to site license categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how does the it services software licensing office choose which software to site license search this site the software licensing office becomes involved in negotiating campus licenses when there is a broad and continuing level of interest across campus in a particular software product in addition they must be able to secure pricing that is significantly lower than campus clients could get on their own the software licensing team does not generally pursue license agreements for software that is already available on campus at a great price such as through the smartmart iprocurement program if you know of a product that you think may fall into this category please submit a helpsu request to software licensing any research you do in advance is helpful including finding out if others on campus share your interest in the product visit the software licensing page for information about other software products need more help submit a helpsu request software licensing stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
